  <note type="source">Smith's Dictionary: "Nicagoras, literary, An Athenian sophist, the son of the rhetorician Mnesaeus, 
    who lived in the time of the emperor Philippus. He wrote an account of the lives of various illustrious men (Βίοι ἐλλογίμων), 
    of Cleopatra of the Troad, and a speech composed on the occasion of an embassy to the emperor..."</note>
